data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and its fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code **won't compile** because the new overload takes `Func<ŌĆ”>` instead of `Expression<Func<ŌĆ”>>`. The fix is dramatically simpler:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual expression-tree construction needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Two sub-changes:**

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column (silent data corruption). EF 10 appends a number (`Street`, `Street1`). If you relied on the shared column, pin names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

- **Nested path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`. Now it maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (full path). To keep old names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

**If you have existing migrations**, EF 10 will generate column renames. Either apply the migration or pin column names to avoid schema changes.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (supports redaction of inlined constants). Add it to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
